HEADWORD: Chiromancy
<hw>Chi"ro*mancy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>chei`r</grk> hand + <ets>-mancy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The art or
practice of foretelling events, or of telling the fortunes or the
disposition of persons by inspecting the hand; palmistry.</def>⟦br⟧
